sections.Trivia:
- The zombie blade featured in this case resembles the Devil King Sword used by Takeshi Onimaru from Yaiba, one of Gosho Aoyama's previous works.
- The names of the suspects come from zombie movies[1]:
- Tetsuto Naitō (内東 徹人) comes from Night of the Living Dead (ナイト・オブ・ザ・リビングデッド ,Naito obu za ribingudeddo?);
- Ria Kawabata (河端 理亜) comes from The Return of the Living Dead, released in Japan under the name Battalion (バタリアン ,Batarian?);
- Takashi Harawaki (原脇 崇) comes from The Evil Dead (死霊のはらわた ,Shiryō no harawata?);
- Kyōko Ejiri (江尻 恭子) comes from Day of the Dead (死霊のえじき ,Shiryō no ejiki?);
- Orie Baishō (倍賞 織江) comes from Resident Evil, released in Japan under the name Biohazard (バイオハザード ,Baiohazādo?);
- Masahachi Ninomiya (二宮 雅八) comes from 28 Days Later (28日後... ,Nijūhachi nighi go?) and 28 Weeks Later (28週後... ,Nijūhasshūgo?);
- Jōji Naitō (内東 丞治) comes from Night of the Living Dead as well as George A. Romero (ジョージ・A・ロメロ ,Jōji Ē Romero?), who wrote and directed the series.
